---
globs: apps/automation-chrome-ext/**
alwaysApply: false
---
- For any flow edits, ask Cursor to:
  1) Generate the **plan** (files touched, commands run, test tags to update),
  2) Execute the change with **typed contracts** + **phased waits**,
  3) Update **E2E slices** under `@smoke`, `@sidepanel`, or the app-specific tag.
- Keep prompts grounded in your **UI integration and flow system** notes; maintain the log-level toggle.
- When adding UI/flow editor features, centralize common UI behaviors (resize/move/minimize) so they propagate to all tool windows (Cursor-flow, Bravado, etc.).
